  "texts": [
    "However, the challenge lies in the massive parameterization of joint probabilities [40], which leads to a huge number of model parameters.",
    "A simplified approach to reducing the number of model parameters is to decompose the joint probabilities by using the left-to-right generation process of sentence sequences.In 1975, Jelinek [41] introduced the N -gram model and applied it to speech recognition tasks [42], also known as the n-gram language model [43,44].",
    "The probability of a word is influenced by the preceding i-1 words, known as the contextual history.",
    "As the number of historical words increases, the amount of data required for this modeling approach also increases exponentially, leading to the \"curse of dimensionality\" [45].",
    "Furthermore, as the historical word sequences become longer, most of the history may not appear in the training data, resulting in a loss of probability estimation."
  ],
